cs.GT, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper is primarily concerned with the performance of the Generalized Second Price auction, which is a mechanism used in sponsored search advertising. As such, it is likely to be relevant to researchers in the fields of game theory (cs.GT), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures (cs.DS), as well as those working on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on equilibrium concepts and social welfare further supports these potential sub-categories.
